    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey @MatthiasKauer I'm afraid the answer is currently no to both your questions. Getting the desired output would require a new `orient` or using a third party encoder as @immerrr  suggested. I'm not averse to adding a new orient, but if you want to take a look the initial changes would need to be made in [objToJSON.c](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/src/ujson/python/objToJSON.c). It'd help if you're familiar with the numpy C-API and the JSON (ujson) code isn't the easiest to follow as there's a fair bit of jumping around and polymorphism going on.\n\nTurning on/off scientific notation isn't supported and is unlikely to be (by me at least), is that just for human readability reasons?\n"
  },
